		<title>13Information on the Colliery</title>
		<content> These are some of the questions we    
 asked on our visit to the pit.        
                                       
                                       
 Q:Approxiamately how much coal is     
 mined each year?                      
 A:In 1983,about 200,000 tons of which 
 125,000 was saleable.                 
                                       
 Q:What is the coal used for?          
 A:Principally for making smokeless    
 fuel.                                 
                                       
 Q:How is it transported?              
 A:Mostly by British Rail,but sometimes
 by truck.                             
                                       
 Q:How many people are employed here?  
 A:569 at the moment,408 underground   
 and 161 on the surface.               
                                       
